## Vision & Mission

**Vision:** Make every paycheck a step forward with one connected ecosystem that turns everyday money management into momentum.

**Strategic ambition:** Become the primary financial home for financially emerging households — the place where paychecks live, bills are managed, gaps are covered, and wealth is built. The goal is to move from being a point solution (today MoneyLion = Instacash in most users' minds) to being a trusted, connected system built around the paycheck.

**The core problem MoneyLion is solving:** Cash flow volatility. 65% of Americans — including 45% of six-figure earners — live paycheck to paycheck. The financial system was built for predictability, not pressure. MoneyLion is uniquely positioned to own this problem end-to-end because it already has the rails (banking, credit, EWA, investing, marketplace) that others address only in fragments.

---

## What We Do

MoneyLion is building the first connected financial ecosystem for financially emerging households. Rather than offering separate products that users stitch together themselves, MoneyLion is moving toward a unified system organized around five jobs-to-be-done: **See, Move, Cover, Plan, Grow**.

| Pillar | What It Does |
|---|---|
| **See** | Know what's coming before it hits — bills, paydays, shortfalls, safe-to-spend balance |
| **Move** | Auto-route income to bills, expenses, and savings; never miss a payment |
| **Cover** | Access cash when short, avoid overdrafts, split big expenses |
| **Plan** | Turn pressure into progress — manage subscriptions, debt, and big upcoming costs |
| **Grow** | Earn cashback, build savings, invest surplus, build credit |

This framework should be referenced when designing any feature — ask which pillar(s) a feature serves, and whether it connects to the others.

