## Business Model

MoneyLion has a diversified revenue model:

| Revenue Stream | Description |
|---|---|
| **Interchange fees** | Revenue from debit card spend on the MoneyLion card |
| **Subscriptions / Membership** | MoneyLion One membership fees, tiered by direct deposit depth |
| **Marketplace referral fees** | Commission earned when users are matched to and take third-party financial products |
| **Interest / lending** | Revenue from EWA (Instacash Turbo fees) and credit products |

The strategic shift underway is moving from **fee-based monetization** (charging for individual product use) toward **system monetization** (recurring membership tied to the depth of the paycheck relationship). More paycheck = lower member price = deeper engagement = higher LTV. Design should support this: features that drive direct deposit adoption and cross-product usage directly support the business model.

