## Company History

MoneyLion was founded in 2013 with the mission to empower anyone to make their best financial decisions. To do so, we focused on how new types of data can personalize, and expand access to, financial services, viewing that data and the models and services we could build on top of them as our moat.

Our first products were in the lending space, using bank transaction data in addition to credit data to understand cashflow, income, expenses, and more. These enabled a more complete and real-time picture of a consumer's profile. In that sense, understanding financial data beyond the credit score is a deep part of our DNA. Over time, with an LTV and retention objective in mind, we expanded products to include depository products like managed investing and bank accounts, with the aim of being there for our customers in times of excess and times of need. We launched Instacash in 2019 to enable users to get access to their paycheck on-demand. 

We also expanded our content capabilities with the acquisition of Malka in 2021 so we could engage, educate, and inspire our users; we then expanded our marketplace capabilities and pushed into B2B distribution models with the acquisition of Engine (then called Even Financial). We view this combination of "advice" - as expressed through PFM features but also content - with "selection" - via the financial products marketplace - as being key for being able to be both trusted and actionable.

With our acquisition by Gen Digital in 2025, MoneyLion's strategy has been updated.
1. We refined our vision, mission, and product strategy to more explicitly focus on the emerging household and their painpoints, as outlined in this document.
2. We expanded our distribution "surface area" with additional owned and operated brands like LifeLock, Norton, and Avast; new channels like Gen's existing partner and employee benefits channels; as well as new international markets. These all represent opportunities for MoneyLion/Engine technologies (under the heading "Financial Wellness Technologies") to support brand and partner goals.

